{"type":"message","id":"73934b95","parentId":"9efd7bed","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:34:32.037Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 14:34 GMT+2] FLEET MODE & SYSTEM CAPABILITIES UPGRADE (Pro Stream).\n\n1.  **Fleet Mode Implementation (`agent_wrapper.py`):**\n    *   Add capability to spawn dedicated workers for `CS2`, `Rust`, `TF2` via `sessions_spawn`.\n    *   Update `/dm_status` to count active workers.\n    *   *Config:* Add `fleet_mode: true` to `openclaw.json` (or internal config object).\n\n2.  **Batch Execution Protocol (PTC):**\n    *   Update `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md`:\n        *   \"Rule: Use `batch_task.py` for >3 API calls.\"\n    *   *Demo:* Create a batch script that scans CS2 + Rust + TF2 targets in parallel locally.\n\n3.  **Lazy Loading & Checkpoints:**\n    *   Update `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md`:\n        *   \"Rule: Use `Select-String` before `read`.\"\n        *   \"Rule: Create checkpoints in `memory/checkpoints/` before refactoring.\"\n    *   Create directory `memory/checkpoints/`.\n\n4.  **Final Capabilities Update:**\n    *   Edit `docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md`: Add \"Section 10: SYSTEM CAPABILITIES\".\n    *   Edit `openclaw.json` (Env/Meta) to reflect new flags.\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Updated `agent_wrapper.py` status.\n    *   Protocol diff.\n    *   Fleet Dashboard preview."}],"timestamp":1771158872035}}
{"type":"message","id":"1ca67b88","parentId":"73934b95","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:34:38.827Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Implementing the Features**\n\nI've started integrating \"Fleet Mode\" in `agent_wrapper.py`. The initial work focuses on spawning workers for Counter-Strike 2, Rust, and Team Fortress 2. Furthermore, I'm updating the `/dm_status` command to reflect these changes and display the status more effectively.\n\n\n**Expanding Fleet Mode Functionality**\n\nI'm now diving deeper into fleet mode. I'm focusing on the configuration updates to enable `fleet_mode` effectively and dynamically. After that, I will move on to adjusting the `/dm_status` command to clearly display worker counts and overall system resource allocation.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771158878459_711","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -R"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771158878573_712","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"openclaw.json"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771158878687_713","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"agent_wrapper.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771158878815_714","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"MASTER_PROTOCOL.md"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":5128,"output":133,"cacheRead":2305,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5261,"cost":{"input":0.010256,"output":0.001596,"cacheRead":0.00046100000000000004,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.012313}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771158872037}}
