{"type":"message","id":"60947e13","parentId":"f6325596","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:35:57.366Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Revising Worker Spawn**\n\nI've pinpointed a crucial flaw in the bot spawning mechanism. The `spawn_worker` function currently utilizes `BOT_SCRIPT` without incorporating necessary arguments. This oversight has now been addressed. Furthermore, I've integrated these changes into the `start_bot` function, which relies on `spawn_worker`. I've also swapped out `start_bot`, `stop_bot`, and `status_bot`\n\n\n**Confirming Variable Scope**\n\nI'm now certain `spawn_worker` is correctly defined and the `BOT_SCRIPT` variable is globally accessible, resolving the initial argument passing concern. Also, I realized I must modify `src/trading_bot.py` to handle the `--game` argument, which would have broken functionality. This change will ensure the bot's proper execution.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771158957359_722","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"src/trading_bot.py","newText":"import time\nimport sys\nimport os\nimport argparse\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Trading Bot Worker\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--game\", help=\"Game to trade (CS2, Rust, TF2)\", default=\"ALL\")\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    game_label = args.game.upper()\n    print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] BOT STARTED ({game_label}). PID: {os.getpid()}\")\n    sys.stdout.flush()\n    try:\n        while True:\n            print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] Bot ({game_label}) running... monitoring markets.\")\n            sys.stdout.flush()\n            time.sleep(5)\n    except KeyboardInterrupt:\n        print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] BOT ({game_label}) STOPPING...\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] BOT ({game_label}) CRASHED: {e}\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()","oldText":"import time\nimport sys\nimport os\n\ndef main():\n    print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] BOT STARTED. PID: {os.getpid()}\")\n    sys.stdout.flush()\n    try:\n        while True:\n            print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] Bot running... monitoring markets.\")\n            sys.stdout.flush()\n            time.sleep(5)\n    except KeyboardInterrupt:\n        print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] BOT STOPPING...\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] BOT CRASHED: {e}\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":74760,"output":783,"cacheRead":72042,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75543,"cost":{"input":0.14952,"output":0.009396,"cacheRead":0.014408400000000002,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.1733244}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771158946819}}
