{"type":"message","id":"ce326e27","parentId":"aef02bc2","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:36:26.429Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reviewing Protocol Details**\n\nI'm currently focused on the `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md` document, preparing to insert the \"10. SYSTEM CAPABILITIES\" section. Before I make any changes, I will re-familiarize myself with the existing content to ensure a seamless integration of the new rules. My goal is to add the new section, which includes the requested rules, within the current structure of the document.\n\n\n**Planning Document Appendage**\n\nI'm now shifting my focus to `docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md`. My plan is to append the \"10. SYSTEM CAPABILITIES\" section, complete with the specified rules. I'll thoroughly review the existing document to ensure the new section is appended seamlessly, maintaining the current formatting and structure.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771158986420_725","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"*   **Market Making:** Provide liquidity at spread > 2%.\n\n*Signed: SYSTEM ORCHESTRATOR*\n\n## 10. SYSTEM CAPABILITIES\n**Objective:** Enhance execution efficiency and stability.\n\n### 10.1. Batch Execution\n*   **Rule:** Use `batch_task.py` for >3 API calls.\n*   **Parallelism:** Distribute target scans across available cores.\n\n### 10.2. Lazy Loading\n*   **Rule:** Use `Select-String` before `read`. Do not load entire files unless necessary.\n*   **Memory:** Keep context window clean.\n\n### 10.3. Checkpoints\n*   **Rule:** Create checkpoints in `memory/checkpoints/` before refactoring.\n*   **Safety:** Always have a rollback point.\n\n### 10.4. Fleet Mode\n*   **Rule:** Use dedicated workers for CS2, Rust, and TF2 when `fleet_mode: true`.\n*   **Isolation:** Ensure worker crashes do not cascade.","oldText":"*   **Market Making:** Provide liquidity at spread > 2%.\n\n*Signed: SYSTEM ORCHESTRATOR*","file_path":"docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md"},"thoughtSignature":""}],