{"type":"message","id":"40780660","parentId":"ce326e27","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:36:26.452Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"edit_1771158986420_725","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  97 *   **Float Sniping:** Buy FT < 0.17 at market price. Sell at +15%.\n  98 *   **Market Making:** Provide liquidity at spread > 2%.\n  99 \n 100 *Signed: SYSTEM ORCHESTRATOR*\n+101 \n+102 ## 10. SYSTEM CAPABILITIES\n+103 **Objective:** Enhance execution efficiency and stability.\n+104 \n+105 ### 10.1. Batch Execution\n+106 *   **Rule:** Use `batch_task.py` for >3 API calls.\n+107 *   **Parallelism:** Distribute target scans across available cores.\n+108 \n+109 ### 10.2. Lazy Loading\n+110 *   **Rule:** Use `Select-String` before `read`. Do not load entire files unless necessary.\n+111 *   **Memory:** Keep context window clean.\n+112 \n+113 ### 10.3. Checkpoints\n+114 *   **Rule:** Create checkpoints in `memory/checkpoints/` before refactoring.\n+115 *   **Safety:** Always have a rollback point.\n+116 \n+117 ### 10.4. Fleet Mode\n+118 *   **Rule:** Use dedicated workers for CS2, Rust, and TF2 when `fleet_mode: true`.\n+119 *   **Isolation:** Ensure worker crashes do not cascade.","firstChangedLine":101},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771158986449}}
